STRINGTABLE 
BEGIN
    IDS_COMBODESC6          "This setting indicates that the combo box will be displayed as a drop down box that displays all the available AutoCAD plot style names."
    IDS_COMBODESC7          "This setting indicates that the combo box will be displayed as a drop down box that displays all the available AutoCAD plot style tables."
    IDS_TEXTBOXFILTER0      "This setting indicates that any key the user presses will be entered into the text box without scrutiny."
    IDS_TEXTBOXFILTER1      "This setting indicates that characters corresponding with the current AutoCAD Angle unit settings will be allowed into the text box."
    IDS_TEXTBOXFILTER2      "This setting indicates that only integers (1 through 9 and 0) will be allowed into the text box."
    IDS_TEXTBOXFILTER3      "This setting indicates that characters corresponding with the current AutoCAD coordinate unit settings will be allowed into the text box."
    IDS_TEXTBOXFILTER4      "This setting indicates that the text entered into the text box will be filtered to determine if it complies with the AutoCAD symbol text definition."
    IDS_TEXTBOXFILTER5      "This setting indicates that the text entered will be automatically converted to upper case only."
    IDS_TEXTBOXFILTER6      "This setting indicates that the text entered will be automatically converted to lower case only."
END

STRINGTABLE 
BEGIN
    IDS_TEXTBOXFILTER7      "This setting indicates that the text entered will be displayed with a password character for security reasons."
    IDS_TEXTBOXFILTER8      "This setting indicates that any key the user presses will be entered into the text box without scrutiny. The text box will also allow the user to enter more than one line of text."
    IDS_BUTTONSTYLE0        "The button will be a standard button with an icon and the same border style as a text button."
    IDS_BUTTONSTYLE1        "The button will be a flat button that uses hot tracking to change appearance when the pointer is over it."
    IDS_BUTTONSTYLE2        "The button will use the AutoCAD 'pick points' icon."
    IDS_BUTTONSTYLE3        "The button will use the AutoCAD 'select objects' icon."
    IDS_BUTTONSTYLE4        "The button will use the AutoCAD 'filter' icon."
    IDS_BUTTONSTYLE5        "The button will not display any border of any kind."
    IDS_BUTTONSTYLE6        "The button will use the current XP visual style for buttons"
END

